The student pilot reported that he was practicing landings on runway 30.  He reported that 
shortly after touchdown (three-point landing) the airplane "suddenly drifted left" as he turned 
from the runway to the taxiway.  The pilot reported that while correcting for the situation, the 
airplane's left wing tip contacted the runway surface.  No preaccident mechanical anomalies 
were reported.
The pilot's failure to maintain directional control while landing.
